main event: Unidentified flying objects with flashing red, green, and orange lights were observed by military and civilian personnel near Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.
interesting points: The objects were unable to be determined in shape and size, but the lights were approximately the size of a matchhead.
The lights would flash and then the red light would be replaced by a flashing orange light.
The objects were moving fast in a northerly direction and just seemed to disappear over the horizon.
A Royal Canadian Air Force jet was scrambled to investigate the sighting, but no identification of the objects could be made.
The sighting lasted for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects with flashing red, green, and orange lights
